  <h1>
   sprite_get_width
  </h1>
  With this function you can find the width of the base resource sprite, with no transforms, in pixels.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">sprite_get_width(index);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      index
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../../The_Asset_Editors/Sprites.htm">
        Sprite Asset
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The index of the sprite to find the width of.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if sprite_width != sprite_get_width(sprite_index)
{
    image_xscale = 1;
}
</code></pre>
  The above code checks the width of the sprite as it is in the current instance and if there is a difference between that and the original base sprite, it resets the x axis scale.
 </body>
